    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** serving as our clear focal point. Boasting an elite 83.19 score against Lorenzen, **Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a prime spot in the #2 hole, making him our highest-floor play for power and average. **Jacob Wilson** (67.19) and **Andy Pages** (68.47) also emerge as core contributors; **Wilson** leverages a significant park advantage and the leadoff spot to maximize his opportunities, while **Pages** draws a favorable matchup against Lorenzen that solidifies his spot in the heart of our order. Even with a high-intensity matchup against McClanahan, **Marcell Ozuna** (61.99) remains a strong start, as the high xERA of the opposing starter provides enough cushion to overlook the challenging platoon split.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today\u2019s bench involved **Nolan Schanuel**, who posted a respectable 55.84 score. Ultimately, he was edged out by the superior efficiency and platoon-adjusted upside of **Dominic Smith** and **Josh Lowe**. While **Schanuel** maintains a stable profile, he lacks the aggressive ceiling required to displace our current outfield configuration. We are also monitoring **Gunnar Henderson** closely; his 54.20 score is suppressed by a tough 15% penalty due to the platoon disadvantage against Cantillo. While he remains in the lineup due to his elite talent floor, his output represents a potential volatility point today. We are keeping **Jackson Merrill** and **Heliot Ramos** in reserve to capitalize on future platoon shifts or rest days, ensuring we preserve our games-played cap for more favorable conditions down the line.",
